## 📦 Prerequisites

Make sure you have the following installed:

- **Node.js** (v16 or later)
- **npm** or **yarn**
- **Git**

---

## ⚙️ Project Setup

### 1️⃣ Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
cd your-repo-name
2️⃣ Install Project Dependencies
npm install

3️⃣ Install JSON Server (Global)

JSON Server is used as a mock backend for products, categories, and orders.

npm install -g json-server

4️⃣ Run JSON Server (Important)

⚠️ You must start JSON Server before running the Next.js application.

json-server --watch db.json --port 5000
Or 
npx json-server --watch db.json --port 5000


The API will be available at:

http://localhost:5000

5️⃣ Run the Next.js Application
npm run dev
